
binding for Gauche for libpq  (to communicate w/  postgresql).

this directory is meant to be  Gauche/ext/pg

The code is based on  what I could understand in the gauche-gtk sources.



** installation:
$ install-cvs
$ ./configure
$ make



** other files:
other files are for a MultiThreaded  application ... work-in-process
pg/mt-copy.scm     the COPY TO/FROM protocol
                   needs some of my other libs (found in the parent dir)

app/migrate.scm    migrate data betwen 2 DBs (w/ a GUI feedback).
                   uses  gauche-gtk


* connecting:
pg-connect   -><pg-handle>     pg . env + conninfo
pg-open   -><pg>               pg-hi ...  :user :port :dbname :host
pg:connect-to-database   pg.db ...  :user :port :dbname :host
  pg:new-handle uses pg-open!

** handles:
<pg-handle> .. stub
<pg>  ... pg-hi    ^^  pg-conn-of ->db
<pg-database>   pg:new-handle ^^


** Artificial objects:
<db>
<namespace>
<relation>

* exec
pg-exec Generics!  <pg-handle> -> <pg-result>
                        <pg>   -> <pgresult>

<db> needs to allocate:


* result
<pg-result> .. stub/C
<pgresult>  .. pg-hi
** Generics/method     pg-nfields

<pg-tuple>
     pg:query-extract-tuples
